#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk00"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hey, sir! Haven't seen you around.\n"
"You sightseeing?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: set_colour (red)
#. 5: reset_colour
#. 6: set_colour (blue)
#. 7: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk01"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Huh? You haven't heard?<2.pa> There's a\n"
"special place where they say you can\n"
"find your true love.\n"
"Folks come from all over to visit, hoping\n"
"for love.<3.pa> It's the <4.se_co>Lover's Pond <5.re_co>on\n"
"<6.se_co>Tuft Mountain<7.re_co>.\n"
"Why don't you go check it out, mister?"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: set_colour (blue)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk02"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I see, I see. There've been lots of visitors\n"
"to this village lately.\n"
"\n"
"They come seeking the special place\n"
"where it's said true love can be found...\n"
"<2.se_co>Lover's Pond <3.re_co>on <4.se_co>Tuft Mountain<5.re_co>.\n"
"But you look like you're probably already\n"
"popular with the ladies, so maybe that's\n"
"not where you're headed."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk03"
msgid "<1.so>Mmm...mmm..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk04"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, yeah, there have been\n"
"people climbing <2.se_co>Tuft Mountain<3.re_co>.\n"
"I wonder if they found love there..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk05"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm going to sleep.\n"
"Come back tomorrow if you\n"
"need something."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
#. 5: pause (long)
#. 6: set_colour (red)
#. 7: reset_colour
#. 8: choice
msgctxt "talk08"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The ol' war chest has seen better days...\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"See, I've gotten really into gambling\n"
"lately, but the gambling hasn't gotten\n"
"really into me, if you get my meaning.\n"
"<2.so>I don't suppose you could spot me...\n"
"say, <3.se_co>100 rupees<4.re_co>, could you? <5.pa>Once I hit it\n"
"big, I'll repay you <6.se_co>10 times<7.re_co> over!<8.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk09"
msgid ""
"<1.so>That's...unfortunate.<2.pa>\n"
"Guess I'll just have to find someone else\n"
"to give me a hand, huh..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: sound
#. 3: pause (long)
#. 4: pause (short)
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
#. 7: set_colour (red)
#. 8: reset_colour
#. 9: choice
msgctxt "talk10"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hey, it's my friend! Thanks for helping\n"
"me out beforeâ€”I really appreciate it.\n"
"\n"
"<2.so>Thing is, though...<3.pa> I'm flat broke again.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"What do you say to spotting me some\n"
"more rupees?<4.pa> I think <5.se_co>100 rupees<6.re_co> would\n"
"be enough. You know I'm good for it!\n"
"You know I'll pay ya back <7.se_co>10 times<8.re_co> over!<9.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Whoa there, buddy!<2.pa>\n"
"No need to rush me!\n"
"\n"
"I won't know the outcome of the bet\n"
"until tomorrow, so you should come\n"
"back then."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: pause (short)
#. 4: set_colour (red)
#. 5: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>My buddy! My pal! <2.pa>I won!\n"
"I hit the jackpot!\n"
"\n"
"It's all thanks to you, too!<3.pa>\n"
"Just like I promised, here's your share:\n"
"<4.se_co>10 times<5.re_co> what you lent me!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
msgctxt "talk13"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I... I lost, buddy.<2.pa>\n"
"I'm broke as broke can be."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk14"
msgid ""
"<1.so>But I can't give up now.<2.pa>\n"
"You'd understand in my shoes.\n"
"You should give it a shot!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk15"
msgid "<1.so>Ah, thanks. I'm most grateful."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "talk16"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I'm gonna go use this to make us some\n"
"money. Don't you worry.\n"
"\n"
"Come back after tomorrow to hear\n"
"how it went."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
msgctxt "talk17"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hold on, you don't have enough to lend\n"
"me any!<2.pa> Ah, man... Don't let me down\n"
"like that."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (short)
#. 3: single_choice
msgctxt "talk18"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Can't even go out fishing in this rain...<2.pa>\n"
"I could go test my luck, though...<3.si_ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (long)
#. 3: set_colour (red)
#. 4: reset_colour
msgctxt "talk19"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Yeah.<2.pa>\n"
"Cloyne runs a <3.se_co>treasure-chest game<4.re_co>.\n"
"It's really fun, especially if you win!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Just so we're clear, though... If my luck\n"
"fails me, I won't be able to pay you back.\n"
"You're OK with that?<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

